[[File:HanPants-ST.jpg|thumb|right|120px|[[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo's]] pants, displaying his second-class Bloodstripes.]]
{{Quote|They don't give out the Corellian Bloodstripe for perfect attendance.|[[Alexsandr Badure]]|<ref name="HSatLL">''[[Han Solo and the Lost Legacy]]''</ref>}}
The '''Corellian Bloodstripe''' was a [[Corellia/Legends|Corellian]] military award for conspicuous gallantry.

==Overview==
{{Quote|First Class Bloodstripes, Corellia's highest honor. Awarded to those who keep fighting despite the odds.|[[Cole Cantarus]]|<ref name="TOR">{{TORcite|type=faction|Republic|Right to Arms|Corellia}}</ref>}}
It was awarded most typically for courage demonstrated after deliberation; it was said that [[Corellian/Legends|Corellians]] believed that anyone can be brave in the heat of the moment, but true heroism came when one ''knew'' that doing the right thing would hurt but did it anyway. Though they could be awarded for many reasons, the majority of the prestigious awards were awarded for courage under fire.<ref name="TOR-codex">{{TORcite|type=codex|First-Class Corellian Bloodstripes}}</ref>

Usually, the Corellian bloodstripes were awarded by the Corellian government<ref name="THG">''[[The Hutt Gambit]]''</ref> to members of the [[Corellian Defense Force/Legends|Corellian Armed Forces]].<ref name="XW:TBW">''[[X-Wing: The Bacta War]]''</ref> However, the award could also be given to [[Police officer/Legends|officers]] of the [[Corellian Security Force]]<ref name="TFW">{{Hyperspace|url=fans/hyperspace/source/nagai11202009/index.html|text=The Forgotten War: The Nagai and the Tofs|int=The Forgotten War: The Nagai and the Tofs}}</ref> or to non-Corellian soldiers who fought for Corellia.<ref name="TOR" />

In everyday dress, the stripe marked by colored piping worn down the side of the trousers. There were two classes of Bloodstripes. The second class was represented by yellow piping; the first class was represented by red piping, and were almost always awarded posthumously.<ref name="HSatCSS">''[[Han Solo and the Corporate Sector Sourcebook]]''</ref> Though not formally recognized by the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Empire]], the [[Imperial Navy/Legends|Imperial Navy]] allowed its servicemen recipients to don the award with their uniforms.<ref name="THG" />

According to some sources a Corellian was entitled to kill without repercussions any other being caught wearing unearned bloodstripes.<ref name="TOR-codex" />

==History==
{{Quote|Corellian Bloodstripes? I never was in the Corellian Military, so I never earned Bloodstripes. Han Solo wears them on his trousers because he went to the Imperial Academy and won them through his bravery.|[[Wedge Antilles/Legends|Wedge Antilles]]|<ref name="XW:TBW">''[[X-Wing: The Bacta War]]''</ref>}}
[[File:Han_Solo_Ally_Pack_art_IA.png|thumb|right|220px|Han Solo wearing his first-class Bloodstripes.]]

During the [[Galactic War]], first class stripes were awarded to the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] heroes who defeated [[Darth Decimus]] and recaptured the [[Legislature Building]] from the [[Sith Empire (Post–Great Hyperspace War)|Sith Empire]] during the [[Battle of Corellia]].<ref name="TOR" />

[[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] won both classes of bloodstripes. His second class stripes were rumored to have been earned for the events surrounding his rescue of [[Chewbacca/Legends|Chewbacca]]; his first class stripes were earned during events that have never been disclosed.<ref name="HSatCSS" /> When Solo was cashiered from [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] service, all the awards and decorations he had earned were literally and systematically ripped off him. He expected to lose his bloodstripes as well, but was allowed to keep them, apparently because they were awarded by the Corellian military and not the Empire.<ref name="THG" /> However, Han Solo wore more often the yellow second class bloodstripes during his career as a [[Smuggler/Legends|smuggler]] since the first class stripes would draw too much attention to him.<ref name="HSatCSS" />

Early in the [[Bacta War]], [[Tycho Celchu/Legends|Tycho Celchu]] suggested that [[Wedge Antilles/Legends|Wedge Antilles]] paint his [[X-wing starfighter/Legends|X Wing]] [[Starfighter/Legends|starfighter]] blue with red stripes in imitation of bloodstripes. Wedge was reluctant to do so as he had never served in the Corellian military and chose a more personal color scheme.<ref name="XW:TBW" />

[[Wraith Squadron]] and [[Rogue Squadron/Legends|Rogue Squadron]] [[Pilot/Legends|pilot]] [[Myn Donos]] also won them during his time as a [[Sniper/Legends|sniper]] with the [[Corellian Defense Force/Legends|Corellian armed forces]].<ref name="XW:IF">''[[X-Wing: Iron Fist]]''</ref>

